values: I think this Christmas is going to be good. Well I suppose it already is Christmas. Merry Christmas. I'm in love with the following... E-V0

So it seems things may be returning to the way they once were. Yep, Brett, Brandon, William and Jmo are all in my basement playing pool. It's been so long since William's even been here. I missed him. The little things, you know.
I knew everything was going to be fine with Allison's court. Well we'll know for sure tomorrow, but it's looking better than we thought.
I swam across I jumped across for you Oh what a thing to do Cuz you were all yellow
I drew a line I drew a line for you Oh what a thing to do And it was all yellow

Leo
Feeling impulsive? Even though you swore you'd keep resisting the urge? Well, good for you. Who says there being truly happy has to have anything to do with behaving yourself? Let go and enjoy some attention.
Will today be a good day? I certainly hope so. I'm worried about Allison of course, and what the outcome will be for her, but for some reason I have a feeling it won't be terrible. Her horoscope looked very positive today & she's got the man on her side, I made sure of that yesterday.
For future reference, Christmas is no longer my favorite time of the year. It's too sad. All I can think about are the fourteen years of good holiday celebrations I had with my family. It's hard to be in the Christmas spirit when I don't even feel like we should be celebrating anything. I helped pick out the tree, but the entire time I was thinking of my father. The way he always chose the largest tree in the lot. That's the way he lives his life - everything to the extreme. Maybe that's why I do the same. But I'm better at controlling it than my 48-year-old father, hmm. Oh well.
I feel like Scrooge.
